        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the beef is browned, add your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>cumin</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>,<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>drained black beans</strong>, <strong>beef</strong> <strong>stock </strong>and <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>and cook over a low heat for 15-20 min or until the sauce has thickened and the beef is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>chilli con carne</strong></p><p>Mix the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lime[s] </strong>with your <strong>smashed avocado</strong></p>",
